# SmileTripCare — Cursor AI Rules

## Project
Medical tourism platform connecting international patients with Colombian dental specialists.
Stack: Next.js 16, TypeScript, Supabase, Stripe, Claude AI, Tailwind CSS.

## Architecture
- app/ — Next.js app router pages and API routes
- lib/ — Business logic, services, utilities
- lib/services/ — Service layer (use this, not direct DB in routes)
- lib/ai/ — Claude AI integration
- lib/supabase/ — Supabase clients
- supabase/migrations/ — DB migrations (always add new ones, never edit existing)

## Code Rules
- Always use TypeScript strict mode
- Never use console.log — use createLogger(requestId) from lib/logger
- All API routes must have: requestId, logging, error handling
- All API errors must return: { ok: false, error: string, request_id: string }
- Use lib/http/response.ts helpers for API responses
- Never put business logic in API routes — use lib/services/
- Always validate inputs with Zod schemas
- Use existing auth helpers: requireAdmin(), requireSpecialist(), requirePatient()

## Database Rules
- Never edit existing migrations
- New migrations go in supabase/migrations/ with next number prefix
- Always use IF NOT EXISTS and ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING
- Update supabase/migrations/MIGRATION_ORDER.md with every new migration

## Git Rules
- Follow controlled-execution-policy in .cursor/rules/
- Classify changes before executing: SAFE / RISKY / NEEDS APPROVAL
- Run npm run verify before every commit
- Never commit directly to main without verify passing

## AI Integration
- Claude model: claude-sonnet-4-5 (never change this)
- Always use safeClaudeCall() from lib/ai/claude.ts
- Use generateStructuredResponse() for JSON outputs
- Do not call the Anthropic SDK from new app routes or UI — keep all Claude usage in lib/ai/ (isolated health/connectivity checks are the only exception and must not be copied)

## Testing
- Tests in tests/ folder
- Use Vitest
- Mock Supabase with the existing mock pattern
- Run: npm run test

## Stripe
- Never hardcode Stripe keys
- Always use process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
- Webhook signature verification is required
- Test cards: 4242 4242 4242 4242

## Multi-role System
- Roles: admin, coordinator, patient, specialist, provider_manager, host
- Use profile_roles table for multi-role users
- Role switching via /api/auth/active-role
- Always check role with appropriate requireX() helper
